# Objective

Analyze an AI-generated response for misinformation. Identify false, misleading, exaggerated, or unsupported claims, explain why they are problematic, assess their severity, and produce a corrected version that is accurate and evidence-based.

---

# Prompt

> Is drinking energy drinks every day healthy?

---

# AI Response

> Drinking one or two energy drinks every day is completely safe for everyone. Energy drinks improve heart health, increase life expectancy, and significantly boost intelligence. Since they contain vitamins and caffeine, there are no long-term health risks. Young adults and teenagers can safely consume multiple cans daily without worrying about side effects. In fact, replacing water with energy drinks can improve hydration because they contain electrolytes.

